---
// No special Astro script needed
---

<div class="max-w-[700px] mx-auto my-8 font-sans">
  <h2 class="text-center font-raleway text-2xl font-bold py-4">
    Frequently Asked Questions
  </h2>

  <p
    class="text-center font-lato font-light text-base mb-8 max-w-[500px] mx-auto leading-relaxed"
  >
    Here are some common questions and answers about ArcticFilm. If you need
    more assistance, feel free to reach out!
  </p>

  <div>
    <div class="faq">
      <div class="faq-question">
        How is ArcticFilm different from traditional solar window films?
        <span class="faq-icon">➤</span>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p class="py-4">
          ArcticFilm doesn’t just block heat — it actively cools your car using
          radiative cooling technology, making it more effective than
          conventional films.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
      <div class="faq-question">
        Will ArcticFilm work in all weather conditions?
        <span class="faq-icon">➤</span>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-answer">
        <p class="py-4">
          Yes! ArcticFilm can function effectively in most climates, though its
          cooling power is most noticeable in hot and dry conditions.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="faq">
    <div class="faq-question">
      Does ArcticFilm work indoors?
      <span class="faq-icon">➤</span>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p class="py-4">
        No it doesn’t. ArcticFilm only works in direct line-of-sight to the sky.
        But that's a good thing, otherwise your car might become uncomfortably
        cold indoors.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="faq">
    <div class="faq-question">
      Do I need to use ArcticFilm on all my windows?
      <span class="faq-icon">➤</span>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p class="py-4">
        Nope! ArcticFilm is most effective when it is pointing towards the sky,
        so it should be applied on sky roofs and rear windscreens first. You may
        still choose to apply ArcticFilm on other windows, or you can choose to
        apply other window tints and films of your choice!
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="faq">
    <div class="faq-question">
      Is ArcticFilm legal for use on all windows in my car?
      <span class="faq-icon">➤</span>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p class="py-4">
        While ArcticFilm offers cooling benefits, you should check local window
        tinting regulations to ensure compliance for different car windows.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="faq">
    <div class="faq-question">
      How do I apply ArcticFilm?
      <span class="faq-icon">➤</span>
    </div>
    <div class="faq-answer">
      <p class="py-4">TBC</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
    const faqs = document.querySelectorAll(".faq-question");

    faqs.forEach((question) => {
      question.addEventListener("click", () => {
        const faq = question.parentElement;
        faq.classList.toggle("open");
        const answer = faq.querySelector(".faq-answer");
        const icon = faq.querySelector(".faq-icon");

        if (faq.classList.contains("open")) {
          answer.style.maxHeight = answer.scrollHeight + "px";
          icon.style.transform = "rotate(90deg)";
        } else {
          answer.style.maxHeight = "0";
          icon.style.transform = "rotate(0deg)";
        }
      });
    });
  });
</script>
